( Reuters : China Daily ) The disaster flattened swathes of the province along with parts of neighbouring Shaanxi and Gansu . But there was public anger after the discovery that many schools fell while other buildings did not , creating suspicion of corruption and corner - cutting in construction . The deaths of the children became a sensitive and taboo subject in the heavily - controlled domestic media and social media websites . Earthquakes frequently strike the country ' s southwest , with twin tremors in neighbouring Yunnan province last September triggering landslides that left at least 80 people dead .